style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(187, 190, 191), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;font-semibold&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px solid; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 600; --tw-font-weight: 600;&quot;&gt;FastAPI pushing to Redis, then worker consuming from Redis, then worker updating Postgres&lt;/span&gt; is accurate.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&quot;text-size-chat leading-[calc(var(--codex-chat-font-size)+8px)] extension:leading-normal mb-1.5&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px solid; margin: 0px 0px 6px; padding: 0px; --tw-leading: 1.5; line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(187, 190, 191), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;font-semibold&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px solid; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 600; --tw-font-weight: 600;&quot;&gt;The CI/CD pipeline arrows should be dashed or separated&lt;/span&gt;, because CI/CD deploys/builds services; it is not part of the live request path.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&quot;text-size-chat leading-[calc(var(--codex-chat-font-size)+8px)] extension:leading-normal mb-1.5&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px solid; margin: 0px 0px 6px; padding: 0px; --tw-leading: 1.5; line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(187, 190, 191), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;font-semibold&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px solid; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 600; --tw-font-weight: 600;&quot;&gt;Monitoring/logging is also an operations concern&lt;/span&gt;, not application business flow. It watches/scrapes/receives logs from gateway, API, worker, and maybe databases.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;" vertex="1">
